Column Comment.0: SOURCE DOCUMENT: unique identifier for the document. For example governmentand regulatory agency forms, operator reports or scout tickets, publications,reference books etc.
Column Comment.1: ABBREVIATION: Abbreviation used for reference type or code
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: SOURCE DOCUMENT TITLE: The full title given to the source document. If thesource document is an article in a publication or journal, this is the title of the Article.
Column Comment.4: DOCUMENT TYPE: The type of document. ie: monthly periodical or technicalpublication or specificiation.
Column Comment.5: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.6: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.7: FIGURE REFERENCE: Reference to the figure in the source document that providesthe detail refered to.
Column Comment.8: PUBLICATION ISSUE: the issue number of the publication or journal that isreferenced.
Column Comment.9: LANGUAGE: The form of a means of communicating ideas or feelings by the use ofconventionalized signs, sounds, gestures, or marks having understood meanings.Usually the language used in a document, proceding, process or appllication.
Column Comment.10: PAGE REFERENCE: The referenced pages in the publication, journal, book etc thatare referenced for this source document.
Column Comment.11: PLATE REFERENCE: the plate in the source document that provides the detail thatis referenced.
Column Comment.12: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.13: PUBLICATION NAME: identifier given to the publication or source document.
Column Comment.14: PUBLICATION DATE: The date of publication of the source document.
Column Comment.15: PUBLICATION YEAR: the year of publication.
Column Comment.16: PUBLISHER: The name of the publishing company for the document. Unvalidated.
Column Comment.17: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.18: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.19: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.20: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.21: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.22: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.23: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.24: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.25: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
